Venice sees around 25 million visitors a year, with the daily total reaching almost 150,000 in the peak season.

Over 75 per cent of visitors are day trippers who head for St Mark's Square, drift around the romantic canals and block the tiny alleyways, placing a huge strain on the medieval city's fragile infrastructure.

Ms Borletti is the former president of the Italian environment group FAI, a nationwide, non-profit foundation established to safeguard Italy's artistic and natural heritage.

