She said the funds raised could be used to finance the city's conservation.

'Venice is slowly dying of tourism, suffocated by summer tourists who eat and run, leaving little or nothing to the city,' Ms Borletti told The Telegraph. 

'For this reason I think we have to protect this city. We should think seriously about the introduction of an entry ticket.'

